An Agriculture Ministry survey hasestimated the nation's 1986/87 crop sugar cane output at 2.14mln tonnes, down from 2.62 mln a year earlier.    Ministry officials said the decline was due to bad weatherand a reduction in the land under sugar cane this season, whichtotals 34,800 hectares, down from 35,700 in 1985/86, they said.    Harvesting stretches from December 1986 to April 1987    Japan's final output will be announced at the beginning ofJune, they said. REUTER&#3;